title: Sound Quest Midi Quest 11 Pro v11.0.0-R2R [deepstatus]
description:
Sound Quest Midi Quest 11 Pro v11.0.0







Midi Quest, the multi-instrument MIDI editor/librarian, is available in three versions: Midi Quest, Midi Quest Pro, and Midi Quest Essentials to complement your studio's requirements.


Midi Quest supports over 700 of the most popular MIDI hardware and instruments from over 50 different manufacturers including Korg, Roland, Yamaha, Kurzweil, Alesis, Waldorf, Kawai, Akai, and E-mu..

You can store, organize, and edit banks and the individual patches, combinations, multis, performances, drums settings, and other SysEx data loaded from your MIDI hardware. Midi Quest is a true multi-instrument editor/librarian designed from the ground up to effectively support multiple MIDI ports, multiple manufacturers, and multiple MIDI devices - including multiples of the same hardware.

Midi Quest "talks" to each MIDI device individually so you can simultaneously send SysEx dumps to as many as 250 different instruments and still edit another instrument - all at the same time. Try doing that with any other editor/librarian...


Highlights
The only actively supported editor/librarian software with fully integrated support for multiple instruments from multiple manufacturers
Integrate MIDI hardware into your computer based music studio with dedicated support for over 650 different MIDI devices (instruments, effects, drum machines, samplers, etc.)
Integrate Midi Quest Pro into any sequencer that supports VST, AU, MFX, or Studio Connections plug-ins and get all of the benefits of your hardware with the ease of software plug-ins
Tired of using stock Patch Name Lists that don't represent the contents of your instrument (factory settings) or selecting your patch changes by number? Create customized Patch Name Lists for your instruments based on the patches currently in your instrument, not just the factory settings. Supports Sonar's Master.Ins file and Cubase/Nuendo Patch Script files
Create custom Patch Name Lists to use with your sequencer, in .midnam XML format for use with Macintosh sequencers and applications such as Pro Tools
Backup, organize, and manage the contents of your MIDI hardware from the comfort of your large, easy to read computer screen
Customize each of your sounds to fit perfectly in the mix. The pro's don't use stock sounds, you don't need to either
Multi-threaded MIDI support allows Midi Quest to update all of your instruments simultaneously
Install any Psicraft editor into Midi Quest and take advantage of Midi Quest's additional features


The possibilities and features of the app are endless!! see more @ https://squest.com/Products/MidiQuest11/Details.html



System Requirements

Windows 32-bit OS Support: Win8, Win 7, Vista, XP
Windows 64-bit OS Support: Win 8, Win 7, Vista, XP
MIDI interface: any MIDI interface with current OS drivers
Windows hardware requirements: any PC capable of running Windows XP, Vista, Win 7, or Win 8 with 100MB HD space
